article.headline: Northwestern St. 70, SE Louisiana 60
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. (AP) -- Clifton Lee and Jermaine Spencer scored 14 points each to lead Northwestern State to a 70-60 win over Southeastern Louisiana Wednesday night. Lee also grabbed nine rebounds and Tyronn Mitchell added 13 points for the Demons (10-5, 3-0 Southland). It was the first time the two teams had met since Southeastern upset Northwestern 49-42 last March, winning the Southland Conference Tournament and advancing to the NCAA Tournament. Ricky Woods led the Lions (8-6, 2-1) with 14 points. Leonard Harden had a double-double of 12 points and 10 rebounds.
